  "original_title": "\u0da0\u0dd3\u0db1 \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0dc4\u0db8\u0dca\u0db6\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0ddc\u0da7\u0da7 \u0d91\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0d85\u0dc0\u0dc3\u0dbb",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The Chinese ship is allowed to come to Hambantota",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Sri Lanka announced in a statement that the Chinese research vessel Yuan Wang 5 was allowed to anchor at Hambantota port from August 16-22.",
        "In the announcement, the Chinese government informed the Ministry of Foreign Affairs that the Yuan Wang 5 ship could reach Hambantota port on August 16 and requested the Ministry of Foreign Affairs to allow it to anchor at Hambantota from August 16-22 to get fuel and other supplies. is shown.",
        "After considering all the issues, Sri Lanka's Ministry of Foreign Affairs today (13) gave permission to the research ship Yuan Wang 5 to anchor at Hambantota port from August 16-22, it is stated in the announcement.",
        "The Ministry of Foreign Affairs once again emphasized that Sri Lanka's policy is to work with all countries in cooperation and friendship.",
        "The Ministry of Foreign Affairs stated that Sri Lanka will always give priority to the security and cooperation of its neighbour."
      ],
